Content:
The price of $ARRR on the onboarding tool is gone down quite a lot compared to when I bought them (not very long ago). Any reason for this? 
I thought that because of the hash rate etc the price would be probably increasing.

Author: BlockTech#6895
Content: @D2D privacyalternatives.com  well it's kind of following mining cost and OTC trade, if everybody is trading at 0,1KMD, onboarding get a bit down to 0,14-0,12, if suddenly OTC trade are around 0,2KMD, onboarding will also follow it near 0,2KMD.

Author: BlockTech#6895
Content: And at the beggining, some people where saying it wasn't worth it to mine ARRR for 0,15KMD when net hashrate was about 60Msol/s that was false information, it's still worth it at 100Msol/s with a price of <0,06KMD.

Author: BlockTech#6895
Content: (GPU not worth it, but ASIC with a price of 0,06KMD you're still making profit =D.)
